Short_summary: Steller‘s sea cow is one of the few very large mammal species to have died out during the recent historical period. It was the largest species of sirenian ever to have existed, and was possibly the largest recent non-cetacean mammal, measuring up to 8 metres long and weighing up to 10 tonnes.

Short_summary: Megaladapis edwardsi is one of almost 20 species of extinct lemurs known from the subfossil record of Madagascar. Many of these species were considerably larger than the indri, the largest living lemur.
